%N A256987 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} H(k)*H(k,2)/k^2 where H(k) is the k-th harmonic number and H(k,2) the k-th harmonic number of order 2.
%D A256987 Ali Shadhar Olaikhan, An Introduction to the Harmonic Series and Logarithmic Integrals, 2021, p. 222, eq. (4.107).
%H A256987 Donal F. Connon, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/0710.4022">Some series and integrals involving the Riemann zeta function, binomial coefficients and the harmonic numbers. Volume I</a>, arXiv:0710.4022 [math.HO], 2007-2008. See p. 153.
%H A256987 Alois Panholzer and Helmut Prodinger, <a href="https://www.mat.univie.ac.at/~slc/wpapers/s55panprod.pdf">Computer-free evaluation of an infinite double sum via Euler sums</a>, Séminaire Lotharingien de Combinatoire 55 (2005), Article B55a.
%H A256987 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-02462-8">(Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer International Publishing, 2019, section 4.25, p. 293, eq. (4.33), section 5.25, p. 320, section 6.25, pp. 398-401.
%H A256987 Eric Weisstein's MathWorld, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/HarmonicNumber.html">Harmonic Number</a>.
%H A256987 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A256987 Equals zeta(5) + zeta(2)*zeta(3) = zeta(5) + (Pi^2/6)*zeta(3).
%F A256987 Equals Sum_{k>=1} H(k,2)/k^3 + Sum_{k>=1} H(k,3)/k^2, where H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2, and H(k,3) = A007408(k)/A007409(k) is the k-th harmonic number of order 3 (Connon, 2007; Olaikhan, 2021, p. 220). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 04 2026
